  "text": "The Chromium Blink rendering pipeline progresses through four critical stages, each implemented in a distinct core module:\n\n## Stage 1: Style Resolution\nThe `StyleResolver` class (third_party/blink/renderer/core/css/resolver/style_resolver.h/cc) is responsible for resolving computed CSS styles for DOM elements. It processes stylesheets, applies CSS inheritance and cascading rules, and produces computed style objects that will be used in subsequent pipeline stages. The key entry point is the `ResolveStyle()` method which takes an element and returns its resolved style.\n\n## Stage 2: Layout Tree Construction\nThe `LayoutObject` class (third_party/blink/renderer/core/layout/layout_object.h/cc) serves as the base class for all nodes in Blink's layout tree. Once styles are resolved, LayoutObjects are created or updated to mirror the DOM structure, with each LayoutObject holding layout-specific information like dimensions, positioning, and box model calculations. The `SetStyle()` method integrates the resolved styles from Stage 1 into the layout object's state.\n\n## Stage 3: Paint Layer Hierarchy\nThe `PaintLayer` class (third_party/blink/renderer/core/paint/paint_layer.h/cc) creates a compositing tree abstraction on top of the layout tree. PaintLayers group LayoutObjects that need to be painted together and manage painting order, clipping, and compositing effects. The `Paint()` method drives the painting traversal through the layer hierarchy.\n\n## Stage 4: Display List Recording\nThe `PaintController` class (third_party/blink/renderer/core/paint/paint_controller.h/cc) acts as the final recording mechanism, capturing paint operations (DisplayItems) into a display list. This display list enables efficient invalidation tracking and rasterization. The `RecordDrawing()` method records individual paint operations that will later be converted to raster graphics.\n\n## Pipeline Summary\nCSS Style Change → StyleResolver (Style Resolution) → LayoutObject (Layout Construction) → PaintLayer (Paint Hierarchy) → PaintController (Display List Recording) → Rasterization. Each component resides in the blink namespace within third_party/blink/renderer/core/ and communicates through well-defined interfaces."
}

